byline.contributor: Matt Furber reported from Minneapolis, and Dave Philipps from New York. Alain Delaquérière and Kitty Bennett contributed research.
byline.original: By MATT FURBER and DAVE PHILIPPS

abstract: Minneapolis police release names of four white men arrested in connection with shooting during Black Lives Matter demonstration that injured five protesters; suspects Allen Lawrence Scarsella, Nathan Gustavsson, Daniel Macey and Joseph Backman are being detained but have yet to be charged.
lead_paragraph: The police on Wednesday released the names of four men arrested in connection with a shooting during a Black Lives Matter protest in Minneapolis outside a police station that injured five protesters.

headline.main: 4 Arrested in Shooting at Black Lives Matter Protest Are Identified
